Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?[DOSKUTSU]=20sdl3-mixer:=20SoundManager=20init/?=
 =?UTF-8?q?shutdown/pause/resume=20=E2=86=92=20MIX=5F*?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Foundation patch of the audio-refactor series (#31, planned 0013-0017).
Replaces SoundManager's SDL2_mixer calls with their SDL3_mixer equivalents
and exposes the singleton MIX_Mixer* through a public mixer() accessor so
Pixtone/Organya/Ogg (patches 0013/0014/0015/0016) can attach their tracks
to it.

This patch alone DOES NOT produce a compiling tree — Pixtone, Organya, and
Ogg still call SDL2_mixer Mix_* APIs that don't exist in SDL3_mixer. The
'compiles + reaches title screen' milestone (per docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 3)
requires the full 0013-0017 series. Numbered as 0017 because it depends on
no other audio-refactor patch (foundation), but is the last in apply-order
because it changes the surface that earlier patches rely on.

Specific changes:
- SoundManager.h: switch include from <SDL_mixer.h> to <SDL3_mixer/SDL_mixer.h>;
  add MIX_Mixer* mixer() public accessor; add private MIX_Mixer* _mixer member
  (with a synchronous-only invariant warning per the cooperative-scheduler
  constraint).
- SoundManager.cpp init(): drop Mix_Init(MIX_INIT_OGG) (decoders are
  registered at compile time in SDL3_mixer; we built with SDLMIXER_VORBIS_STB
  and SDLMIXER_WAVE on); replace Mix_OpenAudioDevice/Mix_OpenAudio with
  MIX_CreateMixerDevice + SDL_AudioSpec; drop Mix_AllocateChannels(64)
  (SDL3_mixer has no fixed channel count — Pixtone manages its own
  MIX_Track pool in patch 0014).
- SoundManager.cpp shutdown(): MIX_DestroyMixer + MIX_Quit replace
  Mix_CloseAudio + Mix_Quit.
- SoundManager.cpp pause()/resume(): MIX_PauseAllTracks / MIX_ResumeAllTracks
  replace Mix_Pause(-1) / Mix_Resume(-1).
- SoundManager.cpp updateSfxVolume(): no-op with TODO(0014). SDL3_mixer's
  volume API is per-track, not global; will be wired through Pixtone when
  the track pool lands. Volume slider non-functional in the interim.

DOS-PORT annotations added per docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 4 (annotate
decisions, not substitutions).
---
 src/sound/SoundManager.cpp | 73 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++----------
 src/sound/SoundManager.h   | 15 +++++++-
 2 files changed, 69 insertions(+), 19 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp b/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
index d29b56e..43110d6 100644
--- a/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
+++ b/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
@@ -33,26 +33,41 @@ SoundManager *SoundManager::getInstance()
 bool SoundManager::init()
 {
   LOG_INFO("Sound system init");
-  if (Mix_Init(MIX_INIT_OGG) == -1)
-  {
-    LOG_ERROR("Unable to init mixer.");
-    return false;
-  }
 
-#if SDL_MIXER_PATCHLEVEL >= 2
-  if (Mix_OpenAudioDevice(SAMPLE_RATE, AUDIO_S16, 2, 4096, NULL, 0) == -1)
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3_mixer registers decoders at compile time (we built it
+  // with SDLMIXER_VORBIS_STB=ON for stb_vorbis OGG, SDLMIXER_WAVE=ON for
+  // WAV; everything else OFF). The SDL2-era Mix_Init(MIX_INIT_OGG) gate
+  // is gone in SDL3_mixer's API — the MIX_Init() below takes no flags.
+  if (!MIX_Init())
   {
-    LOG_ERROR("Unable to open audio device.");
+    LOG_ERROR("Unable to init mixer: {}", SDL_GetError());
     return false;
   }
-#else
-  if (Mix_OpenAudio(SAMPLE_RATE, AUDIO_S16, 2, 2048) == -1)
+
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3_mixer's mixer-creation API is MIX_CreateMixerDevice
+  // (with audio device) or MIX_CreateMixer (memory-only). The SDL2-era
+  // (rate, format, channels, samples) tuple is now an SDL_AudioSpec
+  // struct without the `samples` field — buffer sizing is automatic
+  // (or controlled via SDL_HINT_AUDIO_DEVICE_SAMPLE_FRAMES).
+  SDL_AudioSpec spec;
+  SDL_zero(spec);
+  spec.format   = SDL_AUDIO_S16;
+  spec.channels = 2;
+  spec.freq     = SAMPLE_RATE;
+
+  _mixer = MIX_CreateMixerDevice(SDL_AUDIO_DEVICE_DEFAULT_PLAYBACK, &spec);
+  if (!_mixer)
   {
-    LOG_ERROR("Unable to open audio device.");
+    LOG_ERROR("Unable to open audio device: {}", SDL_GetError());
+    MIX_Quit();
     return false;
   }
-#endif
-  Mix_AllocateChannels(64);
+
+  // DOS-PORT: Mix_AllocateChannels(64) is gone in SDL3_mixer — the new
+  // API has no fixed channel count. Tracks are created on-demand by
+  // Pixtone via MIX_CreateTrack(). The 64-channel cap is preserved by
+  // Pixtone's _slots[64] array; channel-pool-vs-on-demand decision is
+  // documented in docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 3.
 
   std::string path = ResourceManager::getInstance()->getPath("music_dirs.json", false);
 
@@ -125,8 +140,14 @@ void SoundManager::shutdown()
   Organya::getInstance()->shutdown();
   Pixtone::getInstance()->shutdown();
 
-  Mix_CloseAudio();
-  Mix_Quit();
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3_mixer's destroy is MIX_DestroyMixer(mixer); pairs with
+  // MIX_CreateMixerDevice. MIX_Quit() then unwinds the global state.
+  if (_mixer)
+  {
+    MIX_DestroyMixer(_mixer);
+    _mixer = nullptr;
+  }
+  MIX_Quit();
   LOG_INFO("Sound system shutdown");
 }
 
@@ -306,7 +327,12 @@ void SoundManager::runFade()
 
 void SoundManager::pause()
 {
-  Mix_Pause(-1);
+  // DOS-PORT: Mix_Pause(-1) ("pause all channels") becomes
+  // MIX_PauseAllTracks(mixer). All Pixtone tracks attached to our mixer
+  // pause; the music subsystems handle their own track separately below.
+  if (_mixer)
+    MIX_PauseAllTracks(_mixer);
+
   switch (settings->new_music)
   {
     case 0:
@@ -321,7 +347,11 @@ void SoundManager::pause()
 
 void SoundManager::resume()
 {
-  Mix_Resume(-1);
+  // DOS-PORT: Mix_Resume(-1) → MIX_ResumeAllTracks(mixer). Mirror of
+  // pause() above.
+  if (_mixer)
+    MIX_ResumeAllTracks(_mixer);
+
   switch (settings->new_music)
   {
     case 0:
@@ -336,7 +366,14 @@ void SoundManager::resume()
 
 void SoundManager::updateSfxVolume()
 {
-  Mix_Volume(-1, (int)(128. / 100. * (double)settings->sfx_volume));
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3_mixer's volume API is per-track or per-tag (group),
+  // not a global "all channels" setter. SDL2's Mix_Volume(-1, int_0_128)
+  // becomes Pixtone iterating its track pool calling
+  // MIX_SetTrackGain(track, float_0_1) — wired in patch 0014. For now
+  // (foundation-only milestone), this is a no-op so audio still plays
+  // at full volume; SFX volume slider is non-functional until 0014.
+  // TODO(0014): Pixtone::getInstance()->setVolume(settings->sfx_volume);
+  (void)settings;
 }
 
 void SoundManager::updateMusicVolume()
diff --git a/src/sound/SoundManager.h b/src/sound/SoundManager.h
index 1845dc2..765e8ae 100644
--- a/src/sound/SoundManager.h
+++ b/src/sound/SoundManager.h
@@ -3,7 +3,7 @@
 
 #include "../Singleton.h"
 
-#include <SDL_mixer.h>
+#include <SDL3_mixer/SDL_mixer.h>
 #include <cstdint>
 #include <string>
 #include <vector>
@@ -137,6 +137,12 @@ public:
   void updateSfxVolume();
   std::vector<std::string> &music_dir_names();
 
+  // DOS-PORT: Public accessor to the singleton MIX_Mixer*. SDL3_mixer
+  // requires every track / decoder operation to be associated with a
+  // mixer instance. Pixtone, Organya, and Ogg use this to build their
+  // own MIX_Track + MIX_Audio handles. Returns nullptr before init().
+  MIX_Mixer *mixer() { return _mixer; }
+
 protected:
   friend class Singleton<SoundManager>;
 
@@ -152,6 +158,13 @@ private:
   void _start_ogg_track(int songno, bool resume, std::string dir);
   void _reloadTrackList();
 
+  // DOS-PORT: SDL3_mixer Mixer singleton. Owned by SoundManager (created
+  // in init(), destroyed in shutdown()). Pixtone/Organya/Ogg attach their
+  // tracks to this. SDL3-DOS uses a cooperative scheduler — see
+  // docs/SDL3-MIGRATION.md § 3 — so the audio refactor stays SYNCHRONOUS;
+  // do not introduce worker threads accessing _mixer.
+  MIX_Mixer *_mixer     = nullptr;
+
   uint32_t _lastSong    = 0;
   uint32_t _lastSongPos = 0;
   uint32_t _currentSong = 0;
